# http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/PrimaryCrushingOperation
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/PrimaryCrushingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/PrimaryCrushingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/MineralProcessingOperation> .
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/PrimaryCrushingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Process of reducing ore into smaller fragments to prepare it for further  processing and/or so that it can be transported to the processing plant. In \nunderground mines, the primary crusher is often located underground or at the \nentrance to the processing plant."@en .
# 
# http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/Procedure
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/Procedure> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
# 
# http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/ProcessingEquipment
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/ProcessingEquipment> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/ProcessingEquipment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/Equipment> .
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/ProcessingEquipment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "What machinery/equipment is suitable to achieve desired particle size." .
# 
# http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/ProcessingPlant
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/ProcessingPlant> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/ProcessingPlant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Facility where mineral processing is carried out.\nMineral processing (also beneficiation or benefication, ore dressing, mineral dressing, milling) \nProcesses to produce marketable mineral products (e.g. concentrates) from mineral resources. This is usually carried out on the mine or quarry site, the plant being referred to as the mineral processing plant (mill or concentrator). The essential purpose is to reduce the bulk of the ore, which must be transported to and processed by subsequent processes (e.g. smelting), by using methods to separate the valuable (desired) mineral(s) from the gangue. \nThe marketable product of this is called concentrate, the remaining material is called extractive waste from mineral processing (e.g. tailings).\nMineral processing includes various procedures that rely on the mineral's physical characteristics (i.e. particle size, density, magnetic properties, colour) or physico-chemical properties (surface tension, hydrophobicity, wettability)."@en .
# 
# http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/Protocol
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/Protocol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/Protocol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/ControlMeasure> .
# 
# http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/PyroProcessingOperation
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/PyroProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/PyroProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/MineralProcessingOperation> .
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/PyroProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Pyro processing includes the technologies for upgrading of the mineral fractions by drying, calcining or sintering."@en .
